# Weekly BD & Marketing Slides

## Files
- **HTML source**: `tools/weekly-marketing.html` — edit this to update content
- **PDF output**: `tools/BD-Marketing-YYYY-MM-DD.pdf` — regenerate each week
- **Kanban board**: `tools/pipeline-kanban.html` — separate pipeline view

## Slide Structure (12 slides)
1. Title
2. Last Week summary (LinkedIn, Newsletter, Website, BD, Cold Outreach)
3. LinkedIn section header
4. LinkedIn Metrics (website stats + posts list)
5. Newsletter section header
6. Newsletter tracker
7. Website section header
8. **Website Metrics** — pulled live from Amplitude (see below)
9. BD section header
10. **BD Update** — pulled from `deals/pipeline.md`
11. Action Plan / This Week's Focus
12. LinkedIn Best Practices (Meg's tips — static)

## Data Sources

### LinkedIn Posts — "Last Week"
- Read from `/Users/matt/code/uptech/writing/linkedin-posts/`
- Subfolders: `matt/`, `adam/`, `claude/`, `company/`, `appfit/`
- "Last week" = Mon–Fri of the week prior to the meeting date
- Filter files by date prefix (`YYYY-MM-DD-*.txt`) to find posts in range
- Read each file; the post copy is below the YAML frontmatter `---` block

### Website Metrics — Amplitude
- Project: **Uptech Studio Website** (`appId: 545667`)
- Weekly unique visitors: `_active` event, `metric: uniques`, `interval: 7`, `range: Last 30 Days`
- New users: `_new` event, same params
- Top pages: `[Amplitude] Page Viewed` event, group by `[Amplitude] Page Path`, `metric: totals`, `range: Last 7 Days`
- Use `timeSeriesLimit: 0` for top pages (totals only, no per-day breakdown needed)

### BD Pipeline — `deals/pipeline.md`
- Sections map to BD funnel stages: Qualifying → Appointment Scheduled → Presentation Scheduled → Contract Sent
- "Warm Leads" section = follow-up queue
- Note deal owners (Matt / Adam / Claude) and any stale flags

## Regenerating the PDF

```bash
"/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome" \
  --headless=new \
  --print-to-pdf="tools/BD-Marketing-YYYY-MM-DD.pdf" \
  --print-to-pdf-no-header \
  --no-margins \
  --window-size=1280,720 \
  --force-device-scale-factor=1 \
  "file:///path/to/tools/weekly-marketing.html"
```

- Page size is set via CSS: `@page { size: 1280px 720px; margin: 0; }` (16:9, ~landscape)
- Each slide: `width: 1280px; height: 720px; overflow: hidden`
- Rename the output file with the current meeting date

## Updating for a New Week
1. Update the slide title date and `updated` timestamps
2. Read `writing/linkedin-posts/` for last week's actual posts by date
3. Query Amplitude for fresh website metrics (weekly visitors + top pages)
4. Read `deals/pipeline.md` for current BD state
5. Update Action Plan with this week's focus (read `daily standup.txt` and `to-do.txt`)
6. Regenerate the PDF with the Chrome command above
